-- Chinese Smelter Halts Production As Thallium Pollutes River, Xinhua Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-22T03:34:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/chinese-smelter-halts-production-as-thallium-pollutes-river-xinhua-says.html
A smelter in China’s southern
Guangdong province has stopped production because it caused
“excessive levels” of thallium pollution in the Beijiang
river, Xinhua News Agency reported, citing local officials.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
